  "prompt": "What English dubbed anime websites and series are online, free and worth interest?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, there are several websites where you can find English dubbed anime for free, though the availability may depend on region. Here are some popular platforms and a few series worth checking out:\n\n### Websites:\n\n1. **Crunchyroll**: While primarily a subscription service, Crunchyroll offers a selection of free content with ads, including some dubbed series.\n\n2. **Funimation**: Similar to Crunchyroll, Funimation specializes in dubbed anime and has a wide selection. They offer a free tier with ads.\n\n3. **Tubi**: This is a free streaming service that offers a variety of films and TV shows, including a selection of dubbed anime.\n\n4. **Anime-Planet**: This website offers a variety of anime streaming options, including some dubbed titles and allows you to create watchlists.\n\n5. **9anime**: A popular site among viewers, it hosts a large library of anime, including many dubbed options. Be cautious as it may contain ads or pop-ups.\n\n6. **KissAnime (or its updated versions)**: This site has been popular for streaming anime for many years. Note that it can be ad-heavy.\n\n### Worth-Checking Dubbed Series:\n\n1. **My Hero Academia**: A story about a world where almost everyone has superpowers, following a young boy without powers who dreams of becoming a hero.\n  \n2. **Attack on Titan**: A gripping tale of humanity's fight against giants in a post-apocalyptic world.\n\n3. **One Punch Man**: A comedic take on the superhero genre featuring a hero who can defeat any opponent with a single punch.\n\n4. **Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba**: Follows Tanjiro Kamado on his quest to save his sister and avenge his family in a world filled with demons.\n\n5. **Sword Art Online**: A virtual reality game traps players, and the protagonist must navigate challenges to escape.\n\n6. **Death Note**: A psychological thriller where a high school student discovers a notebook that allows him to kill anyone by writing their name in it.\n\n7. **Fullmetal Alchemist: Brotherhood**: A tale of two brothers who use alchemy to find a way to restore their bodies after a failed experiment.\n\n8. **Mob Psycho 100**: A unique story about a young psychic trying to lead a normal life while dealing with supernatural events.\n\nRemember that while many of these websites offer free content, it's always best to support anime creators and the industry by using legitimate platforms whenever possible. Availability can change, so check each service for their current offerings.",
